sections.text:
A lot shall be considered as meeting the requirements of this standard when:
(i)   the total number of defectives as classified according to Section 2.9 does not exceed the acceptance number (c) of the appropriate sampling plan in the General Guidelines on Sampling (CXG 50-2004);
(ii)   the total number of sample units not meeting the count designation as defined in Section II-2.3 does not exceed the acceptance number (c) of the appropriate sampling plan in the General Guidelines on Sampling (CXG 50-2004);
(iii)  the average net weight of  all sample units is not less than the declared weight, provided there is no unreasonable shortage in any individual container;
(iv)  the Food Additives, Contaminants, Hygiene and Labelling requirements of Sections 2.4, 2.5, 2.6 and 2.7 are met.

